title: Man, woman suffer burns after electrical incident in Seattle
text:
Two people have suffered injuries after an electrical incident in Seattle.
The two injured were Seattle City Light employees.
2 @SEACityLight workers injured in electrical vault at Nordstrom HQ. (Woman has serious injuries) @KIRO7Seattle pic.twitter.com/Gr1UQ8UvRG
— Alison Grande (@AlisonKIRO7) October 14, 2015 They were injured in an electrical vault at Nordstrom headquarters.
One woman is left in serious condition.
One man suffered minor injuries.
JUST IN: One woman in serious condition and one man with minor injuries from flash burns after electrical incident, per @SeattleFire
— KIRO 7 (@KIRO7Seattle) October 14, 2015 They have been taken to Harborview Medical Center with flash burns.
The incident occurred at 1600 7 th Avenue in Seattle.
